description:
The Making of Easy Rider

Arts Documentary hosted by Dennis Hopper and Peter Fonda, published by Criterion in 2010 - English narration


Information
------------------------------

In 1969, Peter Fonda and Dennis Hopper changed the face of Hollywood with this seminal counterculture classic. Ushering in a new wave of anti-heroes and introducing mainstream audiences to sex n' drugs and rock n' roll, Easy Rider's influence spread throughout the Hollywood of the seventies, establishing a climate of progressive film-making that now stands as Tinseltown's last Golden Age. Easy Rider's iconic images and soundtrack still resonate with an exhilarating 'freedom', and, although very much a product of 1969, the film has achieved a timeless appeal that grows richer with each passing year. 
Made on a shoestring budget, this legendary road movie was one of the most stylish experiments of the New Hollywood era, and a huge hit upon its release, its success proving instrumental in persuading the big Hollywood studios to invest in more films from young directors.


2)  Shaking the Cage 
This hour-long documentary about the production and cultural impact of Easy Rider was directed by Charles Kiselyak in 1999. It features actor-director-writer Dennis Hopper, actors Luke Askew, Karen Black, Seymour Cassel, and Peter Fonda, cinematographer Laszlo Kovacs, associate producer Bill Hayward, and production manager Paul Lewis.

